<br>
Let me give you a mental picture really fast.<br>
<br>
****You are in sebilis. After 5 hours of LFG you finally get a king group!! WHOOO HOOO!!!. You work your way down to king and you begin to kill the icky shrooms. Group pulls a gating mob_00. (Be it a cleric or something). Group XYZ smacks away at this mob, fighting off a few Complete heals due to resisted stuns. Mob_00 beings to cast Gate. Wizard ABC begins to cast Anchor. ****Your Anchor spell was resisted*** Guess what... NO MORE EVAC. You cant cast for 20 seconds! Here comes the train, so start CR. NO GROUP will ever have 2 wizards for exp group unless you are doing AE groups. AE groups on my server are more rare than trak dropping a cleric BP. <br>
<br>
Verant is missing the big picture. Wizards are already good on big raids. We have lures and evacs. What else do you need beisides mana efficiency? I want all wizards to be able to get EXP groups. As EQ stands at this point in time, wizards just arent needed. NO Verant Int employee can say that a wizard is NEEDED in sebilis. Enchanters are NEEDED, clerics are NEEDED, tanks are NEEDED. Wizards? well... they are a last resort. <br>
<br>
Sorry to burst your bubbles folks. This is our &quot;upgrade&quot; wether you like it or not. I personally hate it and will most likely NEVER use it.  Verant doesnt want wizards in the game and they are doing a good job to force us to other games. <br>
<br>
Eelienu <br>
59 Teleporter/LFG'er<br>
Terris-Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ualeolin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aleolin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 257<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/01 11:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Antigate=Suicide</span><hr size=1> Are you sure you are silenced if it is resisted? If so, and resist rates are high, this spell IS suicide if resisted (mob gates and you can't evac or save the group, which is part of the wizard's role). <br>
Poe may have dropped a bomb on the wizard class. If people start thinking that we can't evac anymore because of this spell, they will ALWAYS chose drood over us or we just won't use this spell in grouping situations. Hah, there goes our great new fix out the window!<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 579<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/27/01 12:03 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Antigate=Suicide</span><hr size=1> An excellent point.  Three things could happen near the end of a fight:<br>
<br>
1.  Mob dies because kill is correctly completed.<br>
<br>
2.  Mob attempts to gate and antigate holds which will hopefully lead to number 1.<br>
<br>
3.  Mob resists antigate, gates, and begins summoning members with you HOPELESS to cast evac because of the silencing.  I'll tell you what, doesn't sound like a very good trade-off to me.  People currently group wizards for evacs.  Do you honestly think after ONE breakdown because of an Antigate that they would EVER invite another wizard again?  I am beginning to see how this &quot;great&quot; enhancement has the potential to spell WORSE group likability for us.  They have some challanges ahead of them.  And dammit they had BETTER figure this one out.<br>
 <p><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith.gif" border="0"><BR><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith3.gif" border="0"><BR>60th Generation Sorcerer of Cazic - Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspace78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>space78</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/27/01 4:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Antigate=Suicide</span><hr size=1> yeah, heres my faith in them figuring it out.<br>
<br>
We at verant have decided the new antigate spell gives the wizard to much power and therefore have put a reagent of 1 diamond per cast and have increased the casting time to 3 seconds with a 30 second repop.<br>
<br>
im just waiting to see some crap like this come threw the boards. it matters not to me personally, ive retired due to their incompetence, but i hate to see all the other wizards out there being screwed over so many times. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 585<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/28/01 7:44 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Antigate=Suicide</span><hr size=1> It is really a psychological thing.  The only way you truly get screwed is if you let them get to you.  By now, most of it bounces off of me so I don't quite have that feeling.  I think they are morons.  But they also don't deserve my energy...  positive, negative, or otherwise.  The just don't deserve it.  So I'll just play and be done with it.  If this problem dictated by the first post, ACTUALLY becomes evident, THEN I'll freak.  And you can bet I'll freak more than ever.  But not before.<br>
 <p><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith.gif" border="0"><BR><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith3.gif" border="0"><BR>60th Generation Sorcerer of Cazic - Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umitebe1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MiteBe1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/28/01 3:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Antigate=Suicide</span><hr size=1> Most of it is psychological for us but the problem lies with others understanding of the spell. To often other classes only recognise the upside of spells and probably wont realize the unfortunate side effect of the silence. I can only hope that resists do not result in the silence or this spell will be of marginal use. <p>MiteBe FameFlinger <BR>
Sorcerer <BR>
Dragon's Claw <BR>
Xegony <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umerco81.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merco81</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/28/01 7:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Antigate=Suicide</span><hr size=1> I honestly am not worrying about it. Mostly because we have the option not to use it. As the person above stated, we are just as useful with our evacs and lures. Big deal, the whole Al'Kabor line is pretty much discarded, so would this spell if we cannot use it. we'll file it in our dusty spellbooks and when the topic of this spell comes up, we'll blame it on Al'kabor, because he is the personification of Verant (chuckle). At any rate, I doubt this spell line would be resisted much, because I'm think it said that it worked like a lure line. don't quote me on this though, I could have read the previous discussion wrong. What is interestion is the .5 sec casting time. Who knows, we'll see when/if it makes it to the utility phase. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umerco81.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merco81</A> at: 6/28/01 5:26:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mildweasel>Mildweasel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/29/01 6:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Antigate=Suicide</span><hr size=1> <br>
